qattracc.attracce:
Sarasota County and Charlotte County were done by thier own in house GIS department.
Because the SWFRPC did not produce those 2 counties critical facilities data, we can not attest to the accuracy of it. While the Charlotte County data apears to be accurate, the Sarasota County data has some blatant errors of which they admit, as in points falling far out in the water. The data here was the latest available they had at the time.

procstep.procdesc: Data originally released by individual counties in 2001. Data was downloaded by GeoPlan in shapefile format from the Southwest Florida Regional Planning Council (http://www.swfrpc.org/maps.htm) in 2001. When received, data was in the following projection: State Plane East, Datum: NAD 27, Units: Feet. The shapefile was then projected to FGDL Albers HPGN.

GeoPlan, during the QA/QC process included the following aspects: 1.) Projected data to FGDL Albers HPGN (See "Map Projection Parameters" below). 2.) DESCRIPT item added based on CATEGORY 3.) Upcased all character records
